PORTRAIT OF SIR PAUL MENZIES OF KINMUNDY (1553-1640). To face p. 140. The original is in Hall of Marischal College. . . .

A fine portrait of a handsome subject, and, notwithstanding the manifest touch of another hand, is substantially what Jamesone left it. Under a bald dome there is a set of fine, regular features, and the whole expression and dress bespeak the gentleman. A rich lace collar, reaching from the ears to a point half way down the breast‚ forms a suitable baekground to the flowing, pointed beard. His arms are painted in the upper right-hand corner, with “ S. P. M.l of Kinmundy, Vive vt Vivas. Anno 1620 AEtatis 67.’'
